The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 6 : Leading steel producers will meet Prime Minister Manmohan Singh tomorrow to discuss pricing issues and other matters related to the industry. The government recently decided to impose an export duty on steel products following a sharp rise in the prices of the metal and its increasing demand-supply mismatch.                             
	 Mumbai, May 6 : The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) proposes to make it easier for foreign companies to operate in India by allowing authorised dealers to extend the validity period and permit the closure of branch and liaison offices of overseas entities in the country.                            
	 New Delhi, May 6 : The government has extended the last date of bid submission, for the third time, for the seventh round of the New Exploration Licensing Policy (Nelp) till June 30 to give more time to prospective bidders to finalise their bidding strategy.                            
	 New Delhi, May 6: The National Council of of Applied Economic Research (NCAER) has stated that the Indian economy could grow by up to 8.9 per cent in 2008-09, despite a global slowdown.                             
	 New Delhi, May 6: The government today said three new mega power projects of 4,000MW each were likely to come up in Orissa soon, in addition to the nine projects already proposed across the country.
                                                                                                                         
